quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  17,105,"We have revealed the Qur’an in Truth, and with the Truth it has come down: and O Muhammad, We have sent you only to give good news to the believers and to warn the unbelievers"
  17,106,"We have divided the Qur’an into sections so that you may recite to the people with deliberation, and We have sent it down in gradual revelations to suit particular occasions"
  17,107,"Say: \"Whether you believe in it or not, it is true that those who were endowed with knowledge before its revelation prostrate themselves when it is recited"
  17,108,"and say, ‘Glory be to our Lord! Our Lord’s promise has been fulfilled"
  17,109,"They fall down upon their faces, weeping as they listen, and this increases their reverence"
  17,110,"O Prophet, say to them: \"Whether you call Him Allah or call Him Rahman; it is all the same by whichever name you call Him because for Him are all the Finest names. Offer your Salah neither in too loud a voice nor in too low a voice but seek a middle course"
  17,111,"and say: \"Praise be to Allah, the One Who has begotten no son and Who has no partner in His Kingdom; nor is He helpless to need a protector, and glorify His greatness in the best possible way"
  18,1,Praise be to Allah Who has revealed the Book to His servant and did not make it complicated
  18,2,It is straightforward so that He may warn about the terrible punishment for the unbelievers from Him and give good news to the believers who do good deeds that they shall have a goodly reward
  18,3,which they will enjoy forever
  18,4,"Further to warn those who say \"Allah has begotten a son"